@node features "Features"

                               Features

-Simple installation: just run the game and play!

-Lightit is a "Workbench" game, so it is meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will automatically be
 resized to an adequate displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-Lightit works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first
version of this game.

1.0: -First release.

1.01: -The game buttons have been changed.
      -The 'About' window have been changed.
      -Now the game window is generated according to the Workbench screen
       size.

1.02: -Bugfix: There was a glitch in the "Easy/Hard game" choosing routine.

1.03: -Some minor changes were made to the program code.

1.04: -Bugfix: The game could crash in some circumstances when its window
       was resized.

1.1: -No more blitting objects! Now the game draws the Light bulbs with
      simple OS friendly commands (it is more usable for systems using
      Amiga emulators such as MorphOS, Amithlon, etc.).
     -Some cosmetic changes were made (the pull-down menus were enhanced,
      the buttons were redrawn...).
     -Other minor changes were made to the program code.

1.11: -The routine that checks when the game window size is too small
       has been revised.
      -The routine that draws the lightbulbs has been revised.
      -Some unneeded program code has been removed.
      -Various minor changes have been made.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Lightit" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, simply click on a lightbulb, this will switch on or off all
the lights located on the same row and diagonally from where that light
is located. Note that a light bulb is on if it is white and off when it
is black. When you complete a game level, Lightit will display a new,
more complex game board, and so on.

  When you begin the game, you have only one lightbulb to change, but as
you complete the game levels, more and more lightbulbs are either turned
on or off, so it becomes more complicated to decide which light has to
be switched...

  If you find that the game is too easy to play, you can play with the
'Harder' game by clicking on the 'Easy/Harder Game' button, this will get
you to the level 15 of the game.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  In the game window, there are 3 buttons:

 -@{b}Restart@{ub}:          Restarts the current game level.

 -@{b}About...@{ub}:         Displays the informations about the game.

 -@{b}Easy/Harder Game@{ub}: Toggles between the Easy and the Harder game.

@endnode

